          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1612276471222-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in your<strong> tomato paste </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1612276476118-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1612276476118-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1612276476118-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1612276476118-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1612276476118-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onions have started to soften, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium and cook for 4-6 min or until the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>meat-free chick'n dopiaza</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1612276489393-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1612276489393-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1612276489393-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1612276489393-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1612276489393-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>meat-free chick'n dopiaza</strong> with the <strong>basmati rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Top with a dollop of your <strong>cultured coconut </strong>and<strong> </strong>your<strong> crispy onions</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>nigella seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
